snippet: The Donald J. Trump Foundation acknowledged on its 2015 tax form that it had used money or assets for a “disqualified person,” or one of the organization’s central people....
lead_paragraph: The Donald J. Trump Foundation acknowledged on its 2015 tax form that it had used money or assets for a “disqualified person,” or one of the organization’s central people.

headline.main: Trump Foundation May Have Used Money to Benefit One of Its Own
headline.print_headline: Trump Fund Cites Benefit to Insider in Tax Filing
